Impulsive flare covered by eclipse in GOES Primary.
Faint, slow CME visible to the NE as seen in SOHO LASCO C2. The source appears to be a slow filament eruption visible to the NE in GOES SUVI 304 starting around 2025-09-27T18:40Z along the NE limb.

Seemingly two jet like CMEs treated as one in this as they are associated with the same source and traveling at similar speeds to the SE in SOHO LASCO C2, C3, GOES CCOR-1, and STEREO A COR2 imagery. T...
Faint narrow CME to the NW visible in SOHO LASCO C2 and C3 imagery. The source appears to be a filament eruption along the NW limb starting around 2025-09-27T15:30Z in GOES SUVI 304.
Extremely faint narrow jet to the SE in SOHO LASCO C2 and STEREO A COR2, too faint to be seen in C3 and GOES CCOR-1. No source has been found.

A very faint narrow jet to the SE in SOHO LASCO C2/C3 and STEREO A COR2. No clear source found but there is minor sparks in AR 14232 at the time.

Narrow jet CME to the ESE in all three coronagraphs (SOHO LASCO C2/C3, STEREO A COR2 and GOES CCOR-1). The source is likely a C3.6 flare from AR 14232 (N02E76) peaking at 2025-09-27T02:40Z.

Narrow CME seen to the NNE in SOHO LASCO C2/C3, STEREO A COR2, and GOES CCOR-1. Source is uncertain; there is no clear source in available UV imagery of the disk.

Narrow faint jet to the SW in SOHO LASCO C2/C3 and GOES CCOR-1 and S in STEREO A COR2. No clear source has been found, however there is continuous activity near ARs 14217 and 14224 on 2025-09-25.

Faint jet to the SW in SOHO LASCO C2/C3 and GOES CCOR-1 and not seen in STEREO A COR2 coronagraph. One possible source could be AR 4217 (S17W65 at the time), marked by a minor brightening in this AR.
Extremely narrow and faint jet seen to the SE in SOHO LASCO C2 and STEREO A COR2. No source has been found.
